      "raw_text": "(Scripps News Association.)\n\n\nDENVER. March 30.-The sheriff\nat Telluride arrived this morning\nwith warrants for w. d. Haywood,\nsecretary and treasurer of the West\nern Federation of Miners. He has\nnot been located.\n\n\nMail advices from Telluride to\nRidgeway state that President Mer-\nGER, charged with flag dissertation,\nobtained bond last night, which was\nsigned by County Judge Wardlaw.\nMercer was released, but was i'm\nmediately rearrested by squad of\nsoldiers and thrown into the bullpen.\nHis three attorneys arrived at Ridge\nway this morning under a military\nguard. 1t is not stated whether they\nwere ordered to leave camp or went\nof their own volition."
    }
